8 Wastes of Lean Manufacturing              Benefits of Lean Manufacturing
  - Unnecessary Transportation              - Optimized Capital
  - Overproduction                          - Reduced Stockholding
  - Unnecessary Motion                      - Faster Production
  - Excess Inventory                        - Improved Quality
  - Waiting (Idle Time)                     - Improved Customer Satisfaction
  - Overprocessing                          - Reduced Operating Costs
  - Defects
  - Unutilized talent


